Dialogs.Dialog: Manaka
Hey, did you go to the New Year's Fireman parade？
Fireman... Wasn't it the First Writing Ceremony？
Geez, that's not it. The Fireman ceremony is an event of fire, right？
Ah, is that so.
The ladder ride... Don't you think it looks interesting？
▲高嶺＊＊▲, I'm curious.
It's a traditional event...
Rather that a traditional event, I just want to ride a ladder！
...Huh？
...I don't know.
(An unexpected star？)
Manaka
I wonder if the kimono is good for the coming-of-age ceremony.
Hmm？ That's sudden.
I heard from a girl in the neighborhood who was worried about wearing a kimono or a suit.
Which one do you want to see？
Hmm, anything is fine.
Ah！ I didn't mean it like that！ Anything looks good on you, I want to see！
... Hehe. Geez.
It's not good, but I'll forgive you. Let's go to the ceremony together, okay？
Yes, of course！
Manaka
Have you ever had a serious snowball fight？
It's a well known game... does it mean it's a fighting game？
Yes. You can't win without a precise strategy and leadership. Sounds fun？
...Emm？
I'm not asking for one, so don't worry about it, okay？
Haha, that's right.
We have to look through it and practice, right？
Huh？
Let's do our best, okay？
(...Did I just confirmed participation？)
Manaka
The sky is really beautiful at this time.
Right. It's different from summer... I wonder if it was Khan or Kean.
Hmm？
Um... is this where Kuhn continues？
That's regrettable. A expected something a little more cute, like a puppy. Yes！
Ku... Hmm？
Ah...
Forget it, you are making fun of me.
(Rabbits are good, but puppies are pretty...)
Manaka
Sumo is really exciting.
Oh, I'll check it.
Of course. Ask for a recording later, but don't let me hear what's inside.
That's right, if you know if it's a win, seeing it will be half the fun.
Right. I had a quarrel with Papa once.
Huh？ What do you mean？
When I came home, he smiled and told me "He won, Manaka！".
He sounds like he was really happy.
I cried and I didn't leave my room for a while.
(His father is scary...)
Manaka
A beautiful peach blossom is blooming in the garden next to you.
Peach blossom？
There are two types, edible fruit peach and ornamental, right？ It's a peach.
Hmm. Does that mean that peach is fake？
It's tiny... are you worried about it？
I' am, ▲高嶺＊＊▲. You care about it too. If it's not edible, we can't try it！
You said you wouldn't be able to eat it, but...
...Yes.
(Did you want to try it.)
Manaka
A relative's child, you know？ She recently entered kindergarten.
Eh, it's such a little girl.
I received a photo of the entrance ceremony, she was so cute...
Did your relatives do the same, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
No. Because it's a boy.
He said he would make me his bride in the future.
...Eh, that easy.
...Hmm？
It's nothing...？
Hehe. "Oh, that's what it was, it looks like！" Might have been nicer.
Manaka
Flower chill is a beautiful word, isn't it？
The sound is nice... But it's not body friendly.
But, that makes me happy.
Why？
...I can tell you it's cold, my hands are cold, right？
...It's getting a little cold, right？
...See.
Yes▼
Manaka
I wonder what I should do on Mother's Day...
What do you do each year？
A handmade Carnation arrangement.
I see, handmade.
I don't have a part-time job, so I can't get expensive things.
Handmade is good. What else？
I often sew accessories that can be used everyday. Sometimes even sweets.
That's amazing...
It's fun to make it, but before that, it's hard to think about what to make.
Every year.
That's right. A birthday is coming soon, so I have to be ready. That's why I practice every day♪
(That's good for her mother.)
That's right, didn't you say you would buy black tea, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Manaka
Yes. Darjeeling in delicious in this season.
Are there seasons for black tea？
Yes, there are.
Oh, did you take tea courses, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Darjeeling has good taste and aroma in May and June. After that, the scent will vanish.
Ceylon tea is good in July and August. There's many kinds of tea, so you can enjoy a lot right？
Huh, I also want to enjoy it.
Then, I will serve you a delicious cup of tea just for you▼
Does your family do anything on Father's Day？
Manaka
Of course. Aren't flowers good for every occasion？
And then, 10 shoulder rubbing tickets. I'll divide each one and make it by hand.
Each one？ That's so authentic.
Actually, I've always thought of making a bag or a tie...
That's no good. I have done the same since I was little.
I think I will continue even after I grow up... Yes, I will continue.
...I'm kidding.
(I'm sure her father is happy each year.)
Manaka
Speaking of June...
What？
What do you think？
Ah, a quiz. Lemme see... the start of the rainy season？
Boo.
Shareholders meetings！
Nope.
Trouble because there are no holidays！
Incorrect.
I'm losing it... a hint, please！
It's embarrassing to say... it's beautiful and nice... it's a girl's dream▼
(Dream... Ah, June Bride.)
Manaka
I want to want to eat physalis.
Emm？
Ah, no！ There's edible physalis called strawberry tomato in season now...
Ah, that was it... Is that different in each area.
It's impossible. It's bitter and makes your stomach hurt.
Hmm？
... is that true？
(▲高嶺＊＊▲ is really positive, somehow...)
Manaka
Phew...
What's wrong？
Ah, I'm sorry. I suddenly remembered you.
A summer gift？ You sighed.
I get a lot every year, me and Mama are busy making lists.
That much？
Papa and Mama interact with a lot of people... I wonder if there's a good way to do it.
Hmm...
If you think about it, won't it be useful someday？
Is that right？
Of course, I can help too.
Manaka
Isn't it hot today？
Yes. I wish I could take a bath in the evening.
That's right...
Ah, you know？ When I was little I thought it would rain in the evening so I stood outside.
Eh, that's bad.
It's a guess, but isn't it more interesting to investigate the origin？
Can you tell me about it？
Isn't it better to investigate by yourself that asking around？
Haha, you look like a Sensei.
▲主人公＊▲.
Yes！
Do your homework, come on！
(If ▲高嶺＊＊▲ was my Sensei, I would be motivated...)
Manaka
Obon lanterns are so beautiful, right？
Ah, the ones that use heat to spin around？
Yes. When I was little, I saw them at my grandmother’s house...
I was curious about how they work, and I tried to see inside, but there was a candle.
Eh！ Did you get an injured！？
I was safe. But it was replaced with a light bulb type after that.
That's right...
Even now, when I get close to an Obon lantern, why does everyone stops me？ I'm not a child.
(I understand why you want to do that...)
Hmm？
No, it's nothing！
It's autumn. I know, the seven autumn herbs...
Manaka
Can you say them？
Hmm...
Hagi, Obana, Kuzu, Nashiko, Jirohana, Fuji Hakama, Kikyo...
Hagi, Obana, Kuzu... Uh？
Please do your best to remember, okay？
Hmm...
Seri, Nazuna, Gogyō, Hakobe, Hotokenoza, Suzuna, Rafuku.
Huh？
Those are the seven spring herbs, don't mistake them.
(It's too hard！)
Manaka
A cloud has appeared.
A while ago, there were fewer clouds.
The oyster worm will bloom, and they smell so good.
When that happens, it means fall is truly here.
Right. I can't keep feeling summer vibes！
Do you still feel summer vibes？
Ah, yes. Well...
Geez, want to wait until next year？
Haha, you're right.
Manaka
Have you finished changing clothes at home？
And you ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Perfectly. I do it along with my school uniforms.
That might be good...
That means you haven't done it, right？
...I wonder.
Geez. But it's okay. That's just how you are.
Someday, I will-
Hmm？
...Until then, it would be useless letting other people do it, so I promise it.
When did Halloween become a major festivity in Japan？ It seems it was recently.
Manaka
When I was younger, I saw my first Halloween costume parade...
What costume did you wear？ A witch？
...Pumpkin.
...Pumpkin？
I don't remember it, okay？
I cried because I wanted to wear the big Jack-o-lantern Mama made.
Eh, and then.
Don't tell me you want to see it... It's embarrassing.
Yes, Yes！ That's why I want to see it！
...I don't know.
(She's afraid...)
Manaka
It's the season for new soba.
Did I say something strange...？
▲高嶺＊＊▲ I've heard that the season for yellow things is all year.
It's because when you like something, you want to know more, right？
I see... I wonder if I feel like that, right？
Emm... Geez.
But maybe...
Hmm, I see.
Geez, why did you talk about this？ This was about soba.
Manaka
I found my first frost.
Oh, did you step on something？
Yes, it crumpled▼
Frost, huh. Do you think it will snow soon？
I want to see the first snow with you.
Yes, I hope we can see it too.
Then, as you can see, we have to make an effort.
How can we do that？
If I'm with you as much as possible, it will increase our chances, right？
I see. We can apply that to other things.
Yes, then the correct answer is to stay together all the time. Hehe.
Manaka
It's about time to order buckwheat flour.
New Year's soba... ▲高嶺＊＊▲, do you make it by hand？
Yes. Papa's soba is delicious.
Your father is amazing！
It's true, okay？ It has a good reputation with my neighbors, so we have it every year.
I try to do it, but Papa is definitely better. It's vexing.
Sounds good...
I want to share it with you▼
(Hooray！)
Ah, it's cold！
Manaka
In times like this, you want to take a bath to warm up, right？
That's nice. But, do you know there is other way？
How？
Come here, ▲高嶺＊＊▲！
Huh？
That won't make you warm, that will make you hot.
That's why I'll resist using hot water.
(You don't have to do that！)
Did you see the New Year's special numbers？
Manaka
I watched a historical drama with my relatives. And a little boy.
I see. I wonder if it's interesting for children to watch historical dramas.
He was having a blast. After that, it was hard for me to be his opponent for sword fighting, you know？
▲高嶺＊＊▲, did you do that？
That's right. With a rolled-up newspaper, we played together.
I see...
Ah, stop. You were imagining me doing it.
Haha. I think that's cool, knight Manaka.
No, I got killed. However, I pretended to be dead and the child cried...
(She's serious about that too...)
How is New Year's with your family？
Manaka
Just normal, I guess？ Prepare the ordered ingredients, cook and display the pine tree with decorations.
I don't think that's normal... Isn't that all handmade？
Yes. Mama makes the main ones, but I also help. Turnip vinegar, Nishiki egg, Chestnut kinton.
Oh, that's amazing. Isn't Japanese cooking hard？
Nothing like that. Each is the same as a normal dish. There's so many, and it takes time.
It seems Papa used to help in the past. I'm here now, so I'm doing my best to clean up instead.
So all your family helps to prepare the celebration, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Aren't celebrations done together？ Therefore, everyone must help.
(Yes, she's right...)
Manaka
It's fun to go out to the garden and see the first signs of spring.
The tree buds, or the flower buds？
Yes. Then hearing the birds chirping. Warblers, White Eye...
The warbler is already here.
Yes. There's food on the tree in the garden. In winter, there isn't much food, so it comes very day.
There are sparrows and pigeons, but the ones who had it hard are the bubuls. They're big, and scare everyone.
Yes, I feel sorry for the bulbul.
I feel sad thinking about it. I have to stop scaring them too.
(Scaring them away...)
Manaka
Both the white and red plums in my neighborhood are in full bloom. It's a great tree.
Wow, white and red. It makes you want to say something.
Hehe, I think the same every time I pass in front.
I think about the entrance ceremony curtain, a red and white hat, and the red and white manju.
...Is that an association game？
That's right. When I looked at the plums there, I started to think it was delicious...
Haha, food over flowers.
The plums are special. I don't usually do that.
And I think it's dango over flowers. Since both come to mind, I don't think of any disadvantage, do you？
(That's what you stick with, so...)
Spring is finally here.
Manaka
That's right. It's getting a lot warmer lately.
And I'm getting sleepy...
Are you lacking sleep？
Spring is like that.
It's the season to wake up from hibernation. I have to get up. Right？
Are you sleepy the most after waking up？ Just 5 minutes after, so I guess spring makes you sleepy.
Geez, I didn't meant it like that. You're just saying that.
(▲高嶺＊＊▲, I don't think you're like that...)
Manaka
More people are wearing mask.
It's pollen season.
The patients who come to our house look so sad with their eyes and nose bright red. I wish I could cure hay fever.
We can invent it once we're adults.
That's right. Maybe we can invent it now？ I'm kidding.
Yes, let's do our best ▲高嶺＊＊▲. We may get the Novenore Award.
Geez, don't be joking around. I was a little serious.
I didn't mean to make fun of you ▲高嶺＊＊▲, I was serious and I want to support you.
Only support？ I don't want it, we have to do it together.
That's... Should I make an effort？
Then, it's decided. Aren't our possibilities limitless？
(She has a serious gaze.)
There is a new program. I wonder if there's something interesting.
Manaka
It's Night Sports News, the contents were interesting.
Did you watch it？
Yes. Even though it's news, it's like a variety program. Since it had minor sports, I learnt a lot.
Oh, it's a big push.
And you know there's a sumo section？ You can practice scenes and wrestling moves, even at home.
I see... A program just for you, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
However, it starts at 10pm... I wish it was a little earlier.
Isn't it good at 10 pm？
No. It's an hour program, so I'm sleepy by the second half. I have to record it, since the sumo section is last.
(So, sumo lover's can't beat sleep...)
Manaka
It's holiday season.
Hmm, do you want to go on a date？
Emm... I meant exactly that.
Haha, a joke.
Geez... But yes, like in a park with a bento...
What's wrong？
I like the park, but I also like my garden. On holidays, my family have lunch there.
Sounds good.
If you'd like, I would want to invite you.
Emm... Can I consider it？
Are you nervous when you're with Papa and Mama？ Then, just us...
(In that case, we can be seen by her father and mother...)
Manaka
A lot of frogs are coming out.
Why do you look so happy？
Don't you like frogs？ Don't you like the little green ones？ Their croaks are really cute too.
I wonder if all girls like frogs.
Every girl likes cute things.
Maybe there are a few girls who think frogs are cute...
That's no true. Geez, I don't know about other girls.
Then, can you tell me？
I can't say it that easy. And, it's something I only understand myself.
(Sounds like what a craftsman would say...)
Manaka
Hey, did you know that kashiwa mochi is very easy to make？
Ah, it's that season... I can make them too.
I shared some with my neighbors, so I don't have any more left...
I see, that's a pity...
Sorry. I'll make some again if I have the opportunity. What color would you like？
Emm, I think white, please？
Only white would be lonely, so I'll try to make it colorful. I'll put mugwort green, red, turmeric yellow.
It was popular with children, so I was asked to make them again.
Wow, that's so cool. I knew it, ▲高嶺＊＊▲ is amazing.
It's not a big deal.
(She's so humble...)
Manaka
It's now 4 am and it's pretty bright outside.
Are you awake at that time？
I just woke up. I thought it was already morning and looked at the clock, I was surprised.
At that time, I was dreaming...
Me too, normally. It's a waste when it's too bright. I wonder if I should go to bed early.
Emm, don't you sleep early enough？
...Can't I？
It's okay, though. I wonder if it's still early enough.
I want to match your life style... So keep it like that.
Manaka
I'll be in trouble if the laundry doesn't dry quickly.
We're in the rainy season. It's sunny now, but...
The sun is coming out, but it's still damp.
I wish I could throw it into the dryer.
Delicate clothes cannot be put in. Depends on the fabric, and if they have embroidery and lace.
Then, cleaning it is a chore.
It's hard to wash something every day.
It's really hard.
And you？ Are you doing your laundry？
I can do it properly.
Geez... I though I had to worry about you being in front of my house.
Hahaha...
Manaka
By the way... do you know what the day of the sea is？
Well, it's the day of the sea.
Not that... I mean, what to do on that day.
I knew it... We have to be grateful towards the sea.
Thank the sea... for the fish or the salt？
And lovers can swim in it！
You said something good again... but yes. We have to be thankful.
Then, thanks to that, we have one more date spot. That's nice.
Geez... Okay, let's do that.
Manaka
Hey, do you like morning glory or hydrangea？
You grow them？
No, I'm talking about yukata patterns. My grandmother will make me a new one.
That so. I'm glad for you.
Yes. I squeezed it into two patterns... I want to know your favorite.
That's some serious responsibility... If you can't decide, why don't you have both？
Don't do that. Granny is working hard.
She's doing it for her cute granddaughter. She can't refuse your begging, ▲高嶺＊＊▲！
Huh, I'm sorry. It's not for me, it's for a younger relative.
Huh？
I'm sorry.
(It's not something to apologize for... but I'm a little disappointed.)
Manaka
It's already fall.
Even though it's midsummer... I still feel the lingering summer heat in fall.
Yes. Therefore, be careful when giving thanks to those who have received a visit in summer.
I see, on the other hand, if it's late, it's no good to have visits in summer.
Huh？
You know, Papa is a person who has decent manners.
Hmm？ Yes.
Mama... not so much, but many of Mama's relatives are very polite.
I see. Is that something I should remember？
Ah！！
Eh？
Yes, I think you should learn. Why not remember it？ For the future.
(Why is ▲高嶺＊＊▲ so happy？)
I wonder if you could help me with my summer vacation homework.
Manaka
Emm！？
Haha, I just wanted to say that. Are you surprised？
Geez. I got anxious when you said that.
Did you truly finish it？
Yes. I always finish my homework.
Heh... I haven't...
...Shall I help you？ Are you all right？
(That was the case after all...)
It's autumn. It's the season of ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Manaka
Me？ Why？
▲高嶺＊＊▲ loves sports and is good at cooking... and you also like books, right？
Hehe, there are so many people who would say that.
Me too. I wonder if I want to try autumn food.
Do you cook？ Oh, maybe you want to learn.
Nope, I just want to eat.
What is that？ Your eyes are full of expectations.
No, I'm just glad you cook so good.
Geez, I'm doing great... Okay, what should I make？
(Hooray！)
Manaka
Papa decided to go to the veterinary to help.
Emm？ ▲高嶺＊＊▲, isn't your dad a doctor for humans？
A friend of his is holding an Animal Welfare Week event, so he's helping.
That was it. What do they do in there？
Open space for animals, dog training class, and a picture-story show. Also shows of guide dogs.
I see, sounds serious.
That's right. Hey, why don't we go there in secret？
It's fine, but why secretly？
Papa doesn't want me to go. I'm in charge of the picture show, but it's embarrassing for just me and Mama. Why？
(I think I understand... It's better if I don't go.)
Manaka
The shopping mall has great offers right now.
I see, so you are checking those things too, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Emm...
Hmm？
Actually, I just talked to a friend... I don't know much.
Haha, so that was it. ▲高嶺＊＊▲ is also an ordinary high school girl.
I am a normal high school girl！
I see, didn't you recently learned how to ask for a burger？
Ah, geez！ Meanie！
Manaka
Do you know why Physical Education Day become known as that？
Because it's autumn！
Boo.
Because autumn sports！
Nope.
Autumn is for sports！
Hehehe, what's that. It's incorrect.
I give up... What is the answer？
Hehe. You know... that？
Hmm？
Geez, I forgot it because it makes you laugh. Then, let's talk later, okay？
(I wonder if that would bother me...)
Manaka
The daffodils in the garden have begun to bloom. They are early this year.
I wonder when they bloom exactly.
From winter to spring. The buds start to bulge around early winter.
Umm... What days winter starts exactly？
November 7th, 8th and so on.
I see... ▲高嶺＊＊▲ you know everything.
Nothing like that. I like flowers, so I'm familiar with them. I have to remember things if I want to become a doctor.
Is there any relationship between that and being a doctor？
Deceases are seasonal. Natural medicine uses seasonal plants.
You truly know everything, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Thank you. I'll accept that compliment.
Some of my classmates were absent today. It seems like flu is already here.
Manaka
School vaccination is yet to come... Right now, patients are waiting in line.
I see, ▲高嶺＊＊▲, your father is busy then.
Especially in recent years. He used to go to nursery schools, but now he doesn't have time.
Does that mean there's more patients？
I'm afraid about flu. I don't think it's bad, but...
...But？
I'm worried that Papa might fall down because he's too busy.
I see, I hope this passes soon...
Manaka
I got a lot of pumpkins. I wonder what I should make.
Pumpkins？
A patient who came brought me some for winter solstice. Do you like to eat pumpkin？
Ah, the winter solstice. Hmm, I wonder if I'll drink pumpkin soup.
That sounds nice. Okay, I'll prepare pumpkin soup.
What about a pumpkin full course？ It's pumpkin from start to finish.
As expected, the first thing is... Hollowing out the pumpkin and stir-fry it into a pumpkin bowl...
(I was kidding...)
Yes, I can do it. Let's make a pumpkin full course！
(▲高嶺＊＊▲ can really make it...)
Manaka
It's the season for general cleaning. I wonder what I should start with.
Oh, I'm overwhelmed.
It's kind of exciting when you think what to do. And it's fun to see the house clean.
Yes, yes, ▲高嶺＊＊▲ can be a good bride like that.
Ah... Geez, no. Cleaning is not the only thing necessary to become a good bride.
▲高嶺＊＊▲ can cook, is attentive, gentle, and perfect.
Huh？
If I'm told that, I would want to do more housework.
